x4freetext: 5 MeV Van de Graaff accelerator.
Six surface-barrier detectors were mounted at
measuring excitation function
8cm*8cm NaI crystal was used to measure the
gamma-ray excitation function simultaneously.
70 cm3 and 25 cm3 Ge(Li) detectors (of 2.7 keV
and 3.2 keV resolution at 1 .33 MeV, respectively) were
used to measure gamma-ray spectra and angular
distribution.
Targets of 4-9 keV thickness at Ea=3.5 MeV were
prepared by vacuum evaporation of MgO, 98.5% enriched
in 24Mg on thin self-supporting carbon foils.
Multi-level R-matrix analysis was performed for
nineteen resonances.
The uncertainty of the absolute energy scale
For energy calibration the Ea=3198.3 keV resonance
was used (from P.M.Endt+,J,NP/A,310,1,1978)
